review_blob: My only two arguments against this beer is: A) a tad hazy. B) It is not produced year round. This beer is by far the best session IPA on the market. Nothing comes close.

On tap. Beer pours golden orange. Two finger head. Nose is mild, citrus.
Balanced malt against orange/grapefruit hops. Superb IPA.
I have never been a big fan of browns. With that said, this is by far the best brown I have ever had. A distant second might be Alesmiths nut brown.
From a bomber pours a medium golden with a two finger head. Nose is mild citrus and slightly piney. Nice malt/hop balance.
Great golf course beer! Not alot going on here. Might as well be water.
Pours black with a mocha colored head. Nose is coffee and nuty.  Taste is also coffee up front. Delious. Maybe a tad too boozey?
Pours an amber color with a two finger head from a bomber. Thin mouthfeel and medium carbonation. Big hops up front with a nice malty back. Great beer for the price!
Pours golden with a two finger head. The nose is pine, tropical fruit and resin. The taste is the same with the addition of band-aid. A little unbalanced as the alcohol really comes through.
beer_name: New Belgium / Alpine Lips of Faith - Super India Pale Ale

review_blob: Pours a hazy amber with a 2 finger head that quickly disapates. Nose is bready and a little funky. Taste isnt that hoppy for a DIPA and has a huge malt backbone.
Pours a golden-amber with a amazing 2 finger head from a 12oz bottle. Nose is a mild sweet pine. Taste is what you would expect of a fine IPA. Balanced hops with malt finish. Great IPA.

Pours a light apricot with a small head from a bomber. Nose is light pine, almost non existent. Taste is quite unbalanced. Kind of arrogant to call your beer Hoptopia and not taste the hops. Not a fan.
Pours an amber orange with a 2 finger head. Nose is a bready pine and the taste is similar. A little too much carbonation for the style, but quite well balanced.
beer_name: Ass Kisser Royal Donk Double IPA

review_blob: Pours an apricot-orange with a nice head. Nose is Danky hops. Taste well balanced and smooth finish. This is one for the rotation.
Pours a medium amber with a nice two finger head. Nose is earthy bread and nuts. Taste isnt very hoppy for a IIPA. Slightly unbalanced malty flavor. Not a fan, wont be buying again.

Bomber. Pours a dark apricot. Two finger head that quickly disapates with moderate lacing. Aroma is mild pine with grapefruit/lemon. Great mouth feel. Taste is piney, citrus and floral with a big malt finish. Damn fine DIPA. Im pairing this with a 5 Vegas Serie "A".
Pours a golden amber with a two finger head that fades quickly. Nose is pine with mild citrus. Taste is the same but with a sweet malt balance. Excellent beer! I will be buying this again.
Pours a pale golden. Lacey head. Nose is pine and gardenia or plumeria. Really good.
Average DIPA. Nose is citrus and mild pine. Taste is citrus and maybe pineapple. Not a big fan. Kind of boring.
22oz. bottle. Golden yellow pour. Decent hoppy nose. Very good representation of the style.

Chased this beer for 2 months. Finally found a 2 week old 500ml Pliny.
Wow! Ive never had a better beer. I cant wait to try Pling the younger if I can find it.
Bottle. Poured light orange. Nose is mild hops.Taste is boring at best. Not a good IPA. Wont be buying this again.
